    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="578"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d578">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 855.48/808</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of the Assistant Secretary of State</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PW1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 18, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: The Belgian Minister tells me that
                    Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HHC1">Hoover</persName> has telegraphed to the Belief
                    Commission in Belgium to begin preparation for future disbandment of the work of
                    the Commission: in other words to prepare to turn it over to the Belgian
                    authorities. <persName corresp="#p_DCdME1">De Cartier</persName> thinks this is
                    a great mistake; that Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HHC1">Hoover</persName> is
                    moving too rapidly although his intentions are good, and wants us to stay Mr.
                        <persName corresp="#p_HHC1">Hoover</persName>’s hand.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d578fn2">According to a note in the files, Mr. <persName
                            corresp="#p_PW1">Phillips</persName> brought the Minister’s views orally
                        to the attention of Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HHC1">Hoover</persName> on
                        Oct. 29.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">W. Phillips</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
